# backend — core

- **Module path**: `github.com/gateforge-iam/gateforge-iam` — all internal imports use this prefix.
- **Stack**: Echo HTTP, Uber FX DI, PostgreSQL, Redis, **global Zap** logging (`internal/logger/`), Sentry/New Relic hooks where wired.
- **Routes**: Two namespaces — root OIDC (`/authorize`, `/token`, …) and app API (`/api/v1/*`) in `cmd/server/routes/router.go`.
- **Security**: Do not add real credentials, API keys, or production URLs to the repo. Treat `cmd/server/.env` as local-only (gitignored).
- **Quality bar**: Match repo-root [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](../../../CONTRIBUTING.md) — `make lint`, `make tests`, `make dep` after dependency edits.
- **IAM-sensitive**: Prefer existing `internal/errors` (`AppError`, middleware) and `internal/constants` for codes; avoid ad-hoc `echo.NewHTTPError` unless consistent with surrounding handlers.
- **Structure**: Respect layer boundaries in `.cursor/rules/go-layering.mdc` (`cmd` = wiring + routes; `internal` = layers below that table).
- **Workflow**: Plan → implement → test → review — see `.cursor/rules/workflow-implementation.mdc`.
- **Agents & commands**: Subagents in `.cursor/agents/`; slash commands `iam:*` in `.cursor/commands/`.
